===Confirmed TX_R Carrier Transactions===

The following TX_R transactions are confirmed on mainnet and demonstrate the carrier P2SH reveal pattern:

<source>
TX_R txid: 77fc29fd9e5124fa85bcc62bb9ab49b8b95b4f4544b521e7589ca980dd1725b4  (mined)
TX_R txid: 238fb58b352a7a2bbcd7eac7565f894ebeba020410b74cc76277f9336041b477  (mined)
TX_R txid: 6551ccceeceb32b77b5930efeaeedea3d6d7a05040f7a84ce2c652ed9fe4c51c  (mined)
TX_R txid: c32635aafa32abf9c89b5e366d647231c143b3fb1b925e51b51a67b6133e7924  (mined)
TX_R txid: a9f2f84b3f2dff84c4505ac680ea6932224eb69c0960d00a5ad8f49df18b4e1e  (mined)
</source>

Each TX_R spends one or more P2SH carrier outputs from its corresponding TX_C. The carrier scriptSig includes the 8-byte tag (e.g., <code>FLC1FULL</code>), the 8-byte HDR8 header, up to three 520-byte data chunks containing the full PQC public key and signature, and the 6-byte carrier redeemScript. Validators can extract the verification material and recompute <code>SHA256(pk || sig)</code> to match against the OP_RETURN commitment in TX_C.

==Deployment==

Phase 1 can be deployed immediately in wallets, tooling, and SPV infrastructure without consensus change.

Phase 2 requires a separate consensus-track proposal and activation plan.

